verbose_text: Hayakawa et al used multiple doses of HMGB1 and showed biphasic effects on proliferation, where low levels of HMGB1 (1-10 ng/ml) increased the proliferation rates of EPCs, but higher concentrations (100-1,000 ng/ml) appeared to have no effect, suggesting that high concentrations of HMGB1 may be deleterious by promoting endothelial inflammation and inducing neurotoxicity.
